The Board, in accordance with its regulations, shall reinstate the license of a physician assistant who has failed to renew the license for any reason if the physician assistant:
Meets the renewal requirements of § 15-307 of this subtitle;
Pays to the Board the reinstatement fee set by the Board;
Submits to the Board satisfactory evidence of compliance with the qualifications and requirements established under this subtitle for license reinstatements; and
Meets any additional requirements set by the Board for reinstatement.
